<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10794</anchor> <rss>erct-001G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001G</addr>  <route>erct-001G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given a <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> by induction:</p><ul><li>a type is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>-2</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when it is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>;</li>
  <li>a type is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>-1</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>;</li>
  <li>for <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, a type <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when for every <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n-1</tex>-truncated</span>.</li></ul><p>So, in particular, a <tex>0</tex>-truncated type is precisely a <em>set</em>. We shall often refer to <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types as <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-types</span></strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10795</anchor> <rss>erct-003P.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003P</addr>  <route>erct-003P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › basic definitions</title> <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10796</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractible type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10797</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10798</anchor> <rss>erct-001J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001J</addr>  <route>erct-001J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sets</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called a <em><strong>set</strong></em> when for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>The notions of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> and <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositional</link> types generate an infinite hierarchy of <em>truncation levels</em> expressing the point after which higher identifications become trivial.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10799</anchor> <rss>erct-001F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Convention</taxon> <addr>erct-001F</addr>  <route>erct-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Indexing of truncation levels</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001F.agda" type="external">erct-001F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>truncation level</strong></em> is an integer <tex>n  \geq  -2</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10800</anchor> <rss>erct-001G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001G</addr>  <route>erct-001G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given a <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> by induction:</p><ul><li>a type is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>-2</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when it is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>;</li>
  <li>a type is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>-1</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>;</li>
  <li>for <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, a type <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when for every <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n-1</tex>-truncated</span>.</li></ul><p>So, in particular, a <tex>0</tex>-truncated type is precisely a <em>set</em>. We shall often refer to <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types as <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-types</span></strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10801</anchor> <rss>erct-001T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001T</addr>  <route>erct-001T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> map</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when all of its <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> are <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types</link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <em><strong>propositional</strong></em> when their fibers are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10802</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractible type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10803</anchor> <rss>erct-001F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Convention</taxon> <addr>erct-001F</addr>  <route>erct-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Indexing of truncation levels</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001F.agda" type="external">erct-001F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>truncation level</strong></em> is an integer <tex>n  \geq  -2</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10804</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10805</anchor> <rss>erct-003S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003S</addr>  <route>erct-003S.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of an <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> type is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10806</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003S</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base cases for <tex>n=-2</tex> and <tex>n=-1</tex> are given by <ref addr="erct-002V" href="erct-002V.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> respectively. In the inductive step, we assume that <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> exhibits <tex>B</tex> as a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and that for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=_Ay</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> to show that for all <tex>u,v:B</tex> the identification type <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is likewise <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>. The result follows from our assumption and the fact that <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is (by <ref addr="erct-003U" href="erct-003U.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>) a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>su=_Asv</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10807</anchor> <rss>erct-003Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003Y</addr>  <route>erct-003Y.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> identification types</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10808</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003Y</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base case for <tex>n=-2</tex> is given by <ref addr="erct-003X" href="erct-003X.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, and the other cases are trivial.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10809</anchor> <rss>erct-003Z.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003Z</addr>  <route>erct-003Z.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Dependent product of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be an arbitrary type and let <tex>B \colon  A \to \mathsf {Type}</tex> be a family of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types. Then the dependent product <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10810</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>, with the base cases following from <ref addr="erct-001A" href="erct-001A.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> respectively. In the inductive step, we need to show that for all <tex>f,g \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> the identification type <tex>f=g</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> assuming the same for the identification types of each <tex>Bx</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-0015" href="erct-0015.xml" taxon="Axiom"/>, <tex>f=g</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex> and the latter is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> by our inductive hypothesis. Therefore, the result follows from <ref addr="erct-003S" href="erct-003S.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10811</anchor> <rss>erct-003W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003W</addr>  <route>erct-003W.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Dependent sum of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003W.agda" type="external">erct-003W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> and let <tex>B \colon  A \to \mathsf {Type}</tex> be a family of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types. Then the dependent sum <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10812</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003W</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>, with the base cases following from <ref addr="erct-003V" href="erct-003V.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-001M" href="erct-001M.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>. In the inductive step, we need to show that for all <tex>u,v \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> the identification type <tex>u=v</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> assuming the same of all the identification types of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>Bx</tex> for <tex>x:A</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-0035" href="erct-0035.xml" taxon="Definition"/>, <tex>u=v</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }  p_*u.2=v.2</tex> and the latter is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> by our inductive hypothesis; thus the result follows from <ref addr="erct-003S" href="erct-003S.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10813</anchor> <rss>erct-002T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002T</addr>  <route>erct-002T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type">Truncation</link> is upward closed</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002T.agda" type="external">erct-002T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>, then it is also <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10814</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002T</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, with two base cases given by <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10815</anchor> <rss>erct-001T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001T</addr>  <route>erct-001T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> map</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when all of its <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> are <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types</link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <em><strong>propositional</strong></em> when their fibers are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10816</anchor> <rss>erct-001P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001P</addr>  <route>erct-001P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001P.agda" type="external">erct-001P.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10817</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-001P</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>.</p>
  <ol><li>
      When <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall from <ref addr="erct-001N" href="erct-001N.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> that being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.
    </li>
    <li>
      When <tex>n=-1</tex>, we recall from <ref addr="erct-001O" href="erct-001O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> that
      being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.
    </li>
    <li>
      For <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, we assume by induction that being <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n-1</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> to prove that being <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. In other words, we must show that <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {isTruncated} \, \mathopen {} \left ( n-1 \right ) \mathclose {} \, A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link> (<ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>).
    </li></ol>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10818</anchor> <rss>erct-001U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001U</addr>  <route>erct-001U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> map</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001U.agda" type="external">erct-001U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given map <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10819</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-001U</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must check that the product <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {isTruncated} \, n \, \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is a <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">proposition</link>; indeed, this is a product of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link> (<ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>) as being an <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> type</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> (<ref addr="erct-001P" href="erct-001P.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>).</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>